import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['cy'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['cy'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cy'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['cy'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('cy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cy values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the relationship between cx and cy values?', wrap=True)

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['name'], data['cx'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max cx value: {data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which location has the highest cx value?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
